Have fun, and don't be afraid to contact me if you have questions.

# Basic Structure

The Themes HTML, IDs, Clases and CSS are based on SMACSS: http://smacss.com/.
It is a one-column Layout based on an 18 Column Grid, with 18 .

20,41,20,41,20,41,20,41,20,41,20,41,20,41,20,41,20,41,20,41,20,41,20,41,20,41,20,41,20,41,20,41,20,41,20,41,20


Main Classes:

.region- 	– A Region is major Container
.page- 		– For the general Page-Types like Homepage, Article-Page, Category-Page
.post-		– Mostly for all types of Post-Representations on the Site, Teasers, as well als full Posts.
.widget_	– These Classes come from Wordpress own's Naming Convention
.box-     


Globally usable Layoutboxes:

.marginalia             - floats left next to the main-content, 3 columns wide, 1st - 3rd column
.apostille              - floats right next to the main-content, 5 columns wide, 14th - 18th column
.broadside         			- 18 columns wide, 1st - 18th column
.mosaic                 - contains 6 subboxes per row, each 3 columns wide, 18 columns wide at all, 1st - 18th column
.troika                 - contains 3 subboxes per row, each 6 columns wide, 18 columns wide at all, 1st - 18th column
.topics                 - contains 2 subboxes per row, each 9 columns wide, 18 columns wide at all, 1st - 18th column

	
*/

/* ========== At first, set Defaults back to zero ========== */
ul,ol,li,dl,dt,dd,h1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6,pre,form,body,html,p,blockquote,fieldset,table,tr,td,thead,tbody{
	margin:0px;
	padding:0px;
	font-weight:normal;
	border:0px;
}

/* Add basic marigins again */

ul, ol, dd{
	padding-left:2em;
}

h2, h3, p, ul, ol, dl, table, pre, iframe {
	margin-bottom:2em;	
}



/* Set the basics 100e2r */

html, body, textarea {
	font:18px/1.45 Georgia, serif;	
	line-height: 145%;		
}

